      "flip_evidence_text": "(ii) ... the Company Board may ... if (A) an unsolicited bona fide written offer is made to the Company and is not withdrawn and the Company Board determines in good faith (after consultation with its financial advisor and outside counsel) that such Acquisition Proposal is a Superior Proposal, and (B) the Company Board determines in good faith, after consultation with outside counsel, that the failure to take such action would result in a violation of the directors’ fiduciary duties under applicable Law; provided, however, that no such Company Change of Recommendation may be made until after (I) at least five (5) Business Days following Parent’s receipt of notice ... and (II) the Company has negotiated in good faith ...",
      "notes": "Claim accurately captures the offer requirements in clause (A), but omits the separate fiduciary-duty determination in clause (B) and the mandatory notice/negotiation procedural requirements, which are part of the full COR standard."
    }
